  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering is complex and involves multiple layers of legislation and regulation at national and international levels. Here are key components:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Proceeds of Crime legislation\n- Mandatory reporting requirements\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n\n3. Key Legal Provisions\n- Criminalizing money laundering activities\n- Establishing reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Implementing customer due diligence procedures\n- Creating mechanisms for asset seizure and recovery\n\n4. Regulatory Oversight\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Central banks\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Regulatory compliance departments\n\n5. Penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Substantial financial penalties\n- Asset forfeiture\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\n6. Compliance Requirements\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Risk assessment protocols\n- Regular internal audits\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining financial system integrity.",
